Gophers coach Ben Johnson was scouting Sunday's basketball game between Wisconsin and Michigan on TV when the postgame handshake line broke out into a scuffle that shook the college basketball landscape. The Big Ten suspended Michigan coach Juwan Howard for five games and fined him for hitting a Badgers assistant. Also fined was Wisconsin coach Greg Gard for not allowing Howard to walk away. Suspensions came for players on both sides for fighting. You've read your complimentary articles for this time period.
